resources.name: Create user with success 201 (/user)
resources.description:
All fields are required

  • name: Must be a string with a maximum of 50 characters.
  • email: Must be a string, valid email and unique with a maximum of 127 characters.
  • password: Must be a string with a maximum of 255 characters and minimum of 8 characters.

Body:

```json { "name": "name_example", "email": "email@mail.com", "password": "abcd1234" } ```

Return (Status 201 Created):

```json { "name": "name_example", "email": "email@mail.com", "id": 1 } ```

resources.name: Fullstack-Afiliados-API
resources.description:
Register your transactions here

Access the repository

This API aims to enable the recording of transactions in a relational database. The project has four routes, each route has a unique function in the API:

  • (POST) /user: register user in aplication.
  • (POST) /user/login: Allows a registered user to log in the application.
  • (POST) /transactions: Records the transactions that are in a 'txt' file (it's necessary to be logged in).
  • (GET) /transactions: Read all transactions recorded in the application (it's necessary to be logged in)

resources.name: User already exists 409 (/user)
resources.description:
If the email passed in the body is already in use, this error will occur.

Body:

```json { "name": "name_example", "email": "email@mail.com", "password": "abcd1234" } ```

Return (Status 409 Conflict):

```json { "message": "Email is already being used" } ```

resources.name: Invalid data 400 (/user)
resources.description:
if the data passed in the fields does not follow the user creation rules, this error will occur.

Body:

```json { "name": 131233, "email": "testemail.com", "password": "12348" } ```

Return (Status 400 Bad Request):

```json { "message": { "name": [ "Expected string, received number" ], "email": [ "Invalid email" ], "password": [ "String must contain at least 8 character(s)" ] } } ```

resources.name: Login with success 200 (/user/login)
resources.description:
All fields are required

  • password: Must be a string.

resources.name: Invalid data 400 (/user/login)
resources.description:
if the data passed in the fields does not follow login rules, this error will occur.

Body:

```json { "email": "emailmail.com", "password": 12345 } ```

Return (Status 400 Bad Request):

resources.name: Invalid credentials 401 (/user/login)

If the email or password is wrong, then this error will occur.

resources.name: Create transactions with success 201 (/transactions)
resources.description:
Uploading the file is required

  • The file format must be ".txt".
  • The ".txt" file needs to have transaction data.
  • You can only use this route if you are logged in.

".txt" file structure

| Campo | Início | Fim | Tamanho | Descrição | | -------- | ------ | --- | ------- | ------------------------------ | | Tipo | 1 | 1 | 1 | Tipo da transação | | Data | 2 | 26 | 25 | Data - ISO Date + GMT | | Produto | 27 | 56 | 30 | Descrição do produto | | Valor | 57 | 66 | 10 | Valor da transação em centavos | | Vendedor | 67 | 86 | 20 | Nome do vendedor |

Body:

Content-Type: Multipart Form; name = file; value = sales.txt

Return (Status 201 Created):

```json { "message": "transactions saved to database successfully" } ```
